* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈrɛkwiˌɛm/|/ˈrɛkwi.əm/}}
* {{hyphenation|re|qui|em|lang=en}}
{{rfap|Theosophical matters, please|lang=Canadian English}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[mass]] (especially Catholic) to [[honor]] and remember a dead person.
# A [[musical]] [[composition]] for such a mass.
# A piece of [[music]] [[composed]] to honor a dead person.  <!--specifically not religious mourners-->

====Usage notes====
The Latin Introit, or opening prayer, for a requiem mass starts with the words:
: ''[[#Latin|Requiem]] aeternam dona eis, Domine, et lux perpetua luceat eis.''
: "Grant them eternal rest, Lord, and may everlasting light shine upon them."

